<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1276,2023]" pageId="6" pageNumber="69">
The gall of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Weld" authorityYear="1926" box="[326,446,1420,1446]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Callirhytis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lustrans">
<emphasis box="[326,446,1420,1446]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="69">A. lustrans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was first described by itself (without the larva or adult wasp) from 
<taxonomicName authority="Wangenh. (Osten Sacken, 1862)" authorityName="Wangenh. (Osten Sacken" authorityYear="1862" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="6" pageNumber="69" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="stellata">
<emphasis box="[1189,1370,1420,1446]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="69">Quercus stellata</emphasis>
Wangenh. (
<bibRefCitation author="Osten Sacken, R. O." box="[229,460,1456,1482]" pageId="6" pageNumber="69" pagination="241 - 259" refId="ref6427" refString="Osten Sacken, R. O. (1862) Additions and corrections to the paper entitled &quot; On the Cynipidae of the North American Oaks and their Galls &quot;&quot;. Proceedings of the Entomological Society of Philadelphia, 1, 241 - 259." type="journal article" year="1862">Osten Sacken, 1862</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. As this name based on gall alone was established before 1931, it is considered valid according to 
<collectionCode box="[299,364,1492,1518]" pageId="6" pageNumber="69">ICZN</collectionCode>
article 23.3.2. Ashmead described a new wingless wasp and erroneously associated it with the gall Osten Sacken had described as 
<taxonomicName authority="Ashmead, 1887" authorityName="Ashmead" authorityYear="1887" box="[552,926,1528,1554]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Acraspis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vaccinii">
<emphasis box="[552,746,1528,1554]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="69">Acraspis vaccinii</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Ashmead, W. H." box="[751,926,1528,1554]" pageId="6" pageNumber="69" pagination="125 - 158" refId="ref4898" refString="Ashmead, W. H. (1887) On the cynipidous galls of Florida, with descriptions of new species and synopses of the described species of North America. Transactions of the American Entomological Society, 14, 125 - 158. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 25076487" type="journal article" year="1887">Ashmead, 1887</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(later transferred to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Burks" authorityYear="1979" box="[1156,1402,1528,1554]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Zopheroteras" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vaccinii">
<emphasis box="[1156,1402,1528,1554]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="69">Zopheroteras vaccinii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by Beutenmüller in 1909a), while reprinting Osten Sacken’s description of the gall (
<bibRefCitation author="Ashmead, W. H." box="[1056,1231,1564,1590]" pageId="6" pageNumber="69" pagination="125 - 158" refId="ref4898" refString="Ashmead, W. H. (1887) On the cynipidous galls of Florida, with descriptions of new species and synopses of the described species of North America. Transactions of the American Entomological Society, 14, 125 - 158. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 25076487" type="journal article" year="1887">Ashmead 1887</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1276,2023]" lastBlockId="7.[151,1437,151,389]" lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="70" pageId="6" pageNumber="69">
In 1913 Beutenmüller described the wasp (
<figureCitation box="[698,824,1600,1626]" captionStart="FIGURES 19–22" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1587,1611]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,413,1563]" captionTargetId="figure-134@7.[151,1436,413,1563]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 19–22. Andricus lustrans. 19. Holotype lateral habitus. 20. Holotype head frontal. 21. Holotype dorsal habitus. 22. Asexual generation gall." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6876441" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6876441/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="69">Fig. 19–21</figureCitation>
) without the gall as 
<taxonomicName authority="Beutenmuller, 1913" authorityName="Beutenmuller" authorityYear="1913" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Andricus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lustrans">
<emphasis box="[1067,1268,1600,1626]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="69">Andricus lustrans</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Beutenmuller, W." pageId="6" pageNumber="69" pagination="243 - 248" refId="ref5011" refString="Beutenmuller, W. (1913) Descriptions of new Cynipidae. Transactions of the American Entomological Society, 39, 243 - 248." type="journal article" year="1913">Beutenmüller, 1913</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, and the same species with its gall a few years later which he named 
<taxonomicName authority="Beutenmuller, 1918" authorityName=", Beutenmuller" authorityYear="1918" box="[985,1432,1636,1662]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Andricus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="impositus">
<emphasis box="[985,1200,1636,1662]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="69">Andricus impositus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Beutenmuller, W." box="[1208,1432,1636,1662]" pageId="6" pageNumber="69" pagination="327 - 330" refId="ref5071" refString="Beutenmuller, W. (1918) Notes on Cynipidae, with description of a new species (Hym.). Entomological News, 29, 327 - 330." type="journal article" year="1918">Beutenmüller, 1918</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. He commented that the gall of 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Beutenmuller" authorityYear="1918" box="[514,655,1672,1698]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Andricus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="impositus">
<emphasis box="[514,655,1672,1698]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="69">A. impositus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Burks" authorityYear="1979" box="[812,934,1673,1698]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Zopheroteras" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vaccinii">
<emphasis box="[812,934,1673,1698]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="69">Z. vaccinii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but the wasp did not match (
<bibRefCitation author="Beutenmuller, W." pageId="6" pageNumber="69" pagination="327 - 330" refId="ref5071" refString="Beutenmuller, W. (1918) Notes on Cynipidae, with description of a new species (Hym.). Entomological News, 29, 327 - 330." type="journal article" year="1918">Beutenmüller, 1918</bibRefCitation>
). Kinsey also separately described this species under the name 
<taxonomicName authority="Kinsey, 1922" authorityName=", Kinsey" authorityYear="1922" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Andricus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="variety" species="dimorphus" variety="verifactor">
<emphasis box="[942,1172,1708,1734]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="69">Andricus dimorphus</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis box="[1232,1342,1708,1734]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="69">verifactor</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Kinsey, A. C." pageId="6" pageNumber="69" pagination="1 - 141" refId="ref5844" refString="Kinsey, A. C. (1922) Studies of some new and described Cynipidae (Hymenoptera). Indiana University Studies, 9 (53), 1 - 141." type="journal article" year="1922">Kinsey, 1922</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, reared from 
<collectingRegion box="[362,430,1745,1771]" country="United States of America" name="Texas" pageId="6" pageNumber="69">Texas</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[442,562,1744,1770]" country="United States of America" name="Oklahoma" pageId="6" pageNumber="69">Oklahoma</collectingRegion>
, and 
<collectingRegion box="[622,736,1744,1770]" country="United States of America" name="Louisiana" pageId="6" pageNumber="69">Louisiana</collectingRegion>
. In 1926, Weld concluded that 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Beutenmuller" authorityYear="1918" box="[1088,1228,1744,1770]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Andricus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="impositus">
<emphasis box="[1088,1228,1744,1770]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="69">A. impositus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Kinsey" authorityYear="1922" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Andricus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="variety" species="dimorphus" variety="verifactor">
<emphasis box="[1284,1436,1744,1770]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="69">A. dimorphus</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis box="[199,309,1780,1806]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="69">verifactor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are the junior synonyms of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Beutenmuller" authorityYear="1913" box="[623,744,1780,1806]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Andricus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lustrans">
<emphasis box="[623,744,1780,1806]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="69">A. lustrans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and transferred the species to 
<taxonomicName authority="(Weld, 1926)" baseAuthorityName="Weld" baseAuthorityYear="1926" box="[1092,1368,1780,1806]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Callirhytis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1092,1211,1780,1806]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="69">Callirhytis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Weld, L." box="[1225,1359,1780,1806]" pageId="6" pageNumber="69" pagination="1 - 131" refId="ref6735" refString="Weld, L. (1926) Field notes on gall-inhabiting cynipid wasps with description of new species. Proceedings of the United States National Museum, 68 (10), 1 - 131. https: // doi. org / 10.5479 / si. 00963801.68 - 2611.1" type="journal article" year="1926">Weld, 1926</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. Most recently, the species was then erroneously synonymized with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Burks" authorityYear="1979" box="[847,967,1817,1842]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Zopheroteras" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vaccinii">
<emphasis box="[847,967,1817,1842]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="69">Z. vaccinii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Burks, B. D." box="[1010,1160,1816,1842]" pageId="6" pageNumber="69" refId="ref5202" refString="Burks, B. D. (1979) Superfamily Cynipoidea. In: Krombein, K., Hurd, P., Smith, D. &amp; Burks, B. (Eds.), Catalog of Hymenoptera in America of North of Mexico. Vol. 1. Symphyta and Apocrita. Smithsonian Inst. Press, Washington, D. C., pp. 1045 - 1107." type="book" year="1979">Burks (1979)</bibRefCitation>
based on Ashmead’s error. The senior author examined the 
<typeStatus box="[569,667,1852,1878]" pageId="6" pageNumber="69">holotype</typeStatus>
specimen and freshly collected materials (
<figureCitation box="[1157,1296,1852,1878]" captionStart="FIGURES 19–22" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1587,1611]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,413,1563]" captionTargetId="figure-134@7.[151,1436,413,1563]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 19–22. Andricus lustrans. 19. Holotype lateral habitus. 20. Holotype head frontal. 21. Holotype dorsal habitus. 22. Asexual generation gall." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6876441" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6876441/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="69">Figs. 19–22</figureCitation>
), reinstating the name 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Beutenmuller" authorityYear="1913" box="[260,381,1888,1914]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Andricus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lustrans">
<emphasis box="[260,381,1888,1914]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="69">A. lustrans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as the species lacks the diagnostic characteristics of 
<emphasis box="[973,1100,1888,1914]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="69">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Weld" baseAuthorityYear="1926" box="[973,1096,1888,1914]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Callirhytis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Callirhytis</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
In the Nearctic 
<taxonomicName box="[1280,1378,1888,1914]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Cynipini">Cynipini</taxonomicName>
phylogeny by 
<bibRefCitation author="Ward, A. K. &amp; Bagley, R. K. &amp; Egan, S. P. &amp; Hood, G. R. &amp; Ott, J. R. &amp; Prior, K. M. &amp; Sheikh, S. I. &amp; Weinersmith, K. L. &amp; Zhang, L. &amp; Zhang, Y. M. &amp; Forbes, A. A." box="[270,478,1924,1950]" pageId="6" pageNumber="69" refId="ref6619" refString="Ward, A. K., Bagley, R. K., Egan, S. P., Hood, G. R., Ott, J. R., Prior, K. M., Sheikh, S. I., Weinersmith, K. L., Zhang, L., Zhang, Y. M. &amp; Forbes, A. A. (2022) Speciation in Nearctic oak gall wasps is frequently correlated with changes in host plant, host organ, or both. Evolution. [in press] https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / evo. 14562" type="book" year="2022">
Ward 
<emphasis box="[337,394,1924,1950]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="69">et al.</emphasis>
(2022)
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Beutenmuller" authorityYear="1913" box="[490,612,1924,1950]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Andricus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lustrans">
<emphasis box="[490,612,1924,1950]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="69">A. lustrans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was recovered as the sister group to an undescribed “pentagonal cluster” gall, both of which are related to 
<taxonomicName authority="Beutenmuller, 1911" authorityName="Beutenmuller" authorityYear="1911" box="[527,977,1960,1986]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Andricus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pisiformis">
<emphasis box="[527,748,1960,1986]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="69">Andricus pisiformis</emphasis>
Beutenmüller, 1911
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Osten Sacken, 1862)" baseAuthorityName="Osten Sacken" baseAuthorityYear="1862" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Andricus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quercusstrobilanus">
<emphasis box="[1033,1354,1960,1986]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="69">Andricus quercusstrobilanus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Osten Sacken, R. O." pageId="6" pageNumber="69" pagination="241 - 259" refId="ref6427" refString="Osten Sacken, R. O. (1862) Additions and corrections to the paper entitled &quot; On the Cynipidae of the North American Oaks and their Galls &quot;&quot;. Proceedings of the Entomological Society of Philadelphia, 1, 241 - 259." type="journal article" year="1862">Osten Sacken, 1862</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. A similar-looking gall was recently described as 
<taxonomicName authority="Melika &amp; Abrahamson, 2021" authorityName="Melika &amp; Abrahamson" authorityYear="2021" box="[870,1432,1996,2022]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Andricus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chapmanii">
<emphasis box="[870,1096,1996,2022]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="69">Andricus chapmanii</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Melika, G. &amp; Nicholls, J. A. &amp; Abrahamson, W. G. &amp; Buss, E. A. &amp; Stone, G. N." box="[1103,1432,1996,2022]" pageId="6" pageNumber="69" pagination="1 - 131" refId="ref6068" refString="Melika, G., Nicholls, J. A., Abrahamson, W. G., Buss, E. A. &amp; Stone, G. N. (2021 a) New species of Nearctic oak gall wasps (Hymenoptera: Cynipidae, Cynipini). Zootaxa, 5084 (1), 1 - 131. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 5084.1.1" type="journal article" year="2021">Melika &amp; Abrahamson, 2021</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, but the adults of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Beutenmuller" authorityYear="1913" box="[339,461,151,177]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Andricus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="70" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lustrans">
<emphasis box="[339,461,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="70">A. lustrans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be easily separated using characters such as the incomplete notaulus (
<figureCitation box="[1292,1374,151,177]" captionStart="FIGURES 19–22" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1587,1611]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,413,1563]" captionTargetId="figure-134@7.[151,1436,413,1563]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 19–22. Andricus lustrans. 19. Holotype lateral habitus. 20. Holotype head frontal. 21. Holotype dorsal habitus. 22. Asexual generation gall." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6876441" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6876441/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="70">Fig. 21</figureCitation>
), and metasomal tergites smooth (
<figureCitation box="[466,548,186,212]" captionStart="FIGURES 19–22" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1587,1611]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,413,1563]" captionTargetId="figure-134@7.[151,1436,413,1563]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 19–22. Andricus lustrans. 19. Holotype lateral habitus. 20. Holotype head frontal. 21. Holotype dorsal habitus. 22. Asexual generation gall." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6876441" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6876441/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="70">Fig. 19</figureCitation>
) (
<bibRefCitation author="Melika, G. &amp; Nicholls, J. A. &amp; Abrahamson, W. G. &amp; Buss, E. A. &amp; Stone, G. N." box="[570,794,186,212]" pageId="7" pageNumber="70" pagination="1 - 131" refId="ref6068" refString="Melika, G., Nicholls, J. A., Abrahamson, W. G., Buss, E. A. &amp; Stone, G. N. (2021 a) New species of Nearctic oak gall wasps (Hymenoptera: Cynipidae, Cynipini). Zootaxa, 5084 (1), 1 - 131. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 5084.1.1" type="journal article" year="2021">
Melika 
<emphasis box="[658,715,186,212]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="70">et al.</emphasis>
2021a
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,151,389]" pageId="7" pageNumber="70">
There is a large series of over 
<specimenCount box="[534,699,221,247]" pageId="7" pageNumber="70" type="generic">100 specimens</specimenCount>
collected from Bronx Park in NY that are identified as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Beutenmuller" authorityYear="1913" box="[1315,1436,221,247]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Andricus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="70" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lustrans">
<emphasis box="[1315,1436,221,247]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="70">A. lustrans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(identified as 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Beutenmuller" authorityYear="1918" box="[306,445,257,283]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Andricus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="70" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="impositus">
<emphasis box="[306,445,257,283]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="70">A. impositus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) collected by 
<bibRefCitation author="Beutenmuller, W." box="[606,840,256,282]" pageId="7" pageNumber="70" pagination="327 - 330" refId="ref5071" refString="Beutenmuller, W. (1918) Notes on Cynipidae, with description of a new species (Hym.). Entomological News, 29, 327 - 330." type="journal article" year="1918">Beutenmüller (1918)</bibRefCitation>
at 
<collectionCode box="[875,963,257,283]" country="USA" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/142r-0w94" name="Smithsonian Institution, National Museum of Natural History" pageId="7" pageNumber="70" type="Museum">NMNH</collectionCode>
, which he stated as common in the region but is becoming urbanized. There are no current records of this species on iNaturalist outside of 
<collectionCode box="[1245,1285,292,318]" pageId="7" pageNumber="70">TX</collectionCode>
, which could suggest a reduction in their distribution, despite 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wangenh. (Osten Sacken" authorityYear="1862" box="[693,810,327,353]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="7" pageNumber="70" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="stellata">
<emphasis box="[693,810,327,353]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="70">Q. stellata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
being found across eastern 
<collectingCountry box="[1124,1163,327,353]" name="United States of America" pageId="7" pageNumber="70">US</collectingCountry>
. Additional host records include 
<taxonomicName authority="(Torr.) C. H. Mull. (Weld 1959)" authorityName="C. H. Mull. (Weld" authorityYear="1959" box="[241,933,362,389]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="7" pageNumber="70" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="sinuata" variety="breviloba">
<emphasis box="[241,585,363,389]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="70">Quercus sinuata var. breviloba</emphasis>
(Torr.) C.H.Mull. (
<bibRefCitation author="Weld, L. H." box="[800,924,362,389]" pageId="7" pageNumber="70" refId="ref6865" refString="Weld, L. H. (1959) Cynipid galls of the Eastern United States. Privately printed, Ann Arbor, Michigan, 124 pp." type="book" year="1959">Weld 1959</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
